s on Amazon EC2. I have chosen instance type r3.2xlarge. As amazon claimed, it has 8 vcpu. Each vCPU is a hyperthread of an Intel Xeon core for M3, C4, C3, R3, HS1, G2, I2, and D2. (from <i><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/instance-types/" target="_blank">https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/instance-types/</a>)</i><br clear="all"><div><br></div><div>However, when I try to run experiments on 4 machines, each with 8 slots. OPENMPI reminds me that I am oversubscribing.</div><div><br></div><div>Does anyone know the reason? Thanks in advance!</div><div><br></div><div><br></div>-- <br><div><div dir="ltr">Best Regards.<br>---<br>Xing FENG<div>PhD Candidate<br>Database Research Group<br><br></div><div>School of Computer Science and Engineering<div>University of New South Wales<br></div>NSW 2052, Sydney<br></div><div><br></div><div>Phone: <a href="tel:%28%2B61%29%20413%20857%20288" value="+61413857288" target="_blank">(+61) 413 857 288</a></div></div></div>
